  "properties": {
    "title": "Crop fields (2025) - focus on NUS crops",
    "description": "Amazonian tubers classified as Neglected and Underutilized Crop Species (NUS crops) in each farmers field, accurately documenting the characteristics of these species in situ. This process generated a comprehensive dataset comprising seven different crops: cassava (Manihot esculenta), sweet potato (Ipomoea batatas), aerial potato (Dioscorea bulbifera L.), achipa or chuin (Pachyrhizus tuberosus), pituca (Colocasia spp., Xanthosoma spp.), dale-dale (Calathea allouia), and sacha papa (Dioscorea bulbifera). Overall, the study captured the main characteristics of 683 varieties/404 species recorded across 273 mapped plots from 221 farmer households. The dataset is organized into: A) Household information, B) Field information and land-use history, C) Species names, D) Variety names, and E) Community collection points of NUS crops",
